title: For Sale:  VZ2008 rifle - new, unfired + EXTRAS
postcontent:
For sale is a brand-new, unfired VZ2008 chambered in 7.62x39. This rifle has been a safe queen; I bought it new less than a year ago and never fired it. I've moved in another direction with the gun collection, so off it goes. 

The rifle is in absolutely perfect condition. It's been kept in a humidity-controlled safe and babied. I've never oiled it, so it's just like it came from the factory. Included are five magazines (approx $25 value each) and four of them are still sealed from the factory. The original bayonet is also included. The leather scabbard has some interesting graffiti drawn on it, which I'm guessing was done by Serbian soldiers during the 1990s. There is a Metallica logo and a reference to the band Dead Kennedys, along with some Cyrillic writing and a few other things including the words "fuck off." Although the rifle is brand new, the bayonet probably saw action in the Balkan conflicts during the 1990s.

In addition to all of the above, I'm including a brand new, never-used Czech military surplus messenger bag. It is a green bag with a rubberized coating to protect against water. It's my understanding that it was originally intended to hold a radio.

title: For Sale:  Mueller Optics 3-10X44 TAC II Scope and Target Turrets
postcontent:
This 3-10x44 offers excellent optics, a comparatively wide field of view and adequate eye relief for use on high power rifles.


The 3-10x44 Tac II is built on a one-inch diameter, matte black anodized, aluminum alloy main tube. Inside that tube are fully multi-coated lenses. The fingertip adjustable, ¼ MOA windage and elevation adjustments offer a whopping 95 MOA range and the mildot reticle always remains centered. Eyepiece focus is of the European fast-focus style. All Mueller Tac II scopes are covered by Mueller's transferable Limited Lifetime Warranty.


It may be something of a trade secret, but the fact is that the 3-10x44 Tac II is produced for Mueller in the same factory that makes the very highly regarded Sightron SIIB Big Sky riflescopes. This accounts for its similarity in many ways to a Sightron Big Sky.


Item number: MTAC31044


 Fully multi-coated, camera quality, crystal lenses for superior brightness and contrast 
 All weather high-torque power change ring 
 ¼″ windage and elevation adjustments with audible click stops and easy fingertip turrets (no tools required) 
 Maximum internal adj.: Elevation 95moa / Windage 90 MOA 
 Parallax setting: 100 yards 
 FOV @ 100 yards: 36′–11.4′ 
 Weight: 15.5 oz 
 Eye relief: 3.40″ 
 Overall length: 12.625″ 
 Exit pupil: 14.6mm–4.4mm 
 Fast focus ocular bell 
 Nitrogen filled, waterproof, fog proof and shockproof 
 1″ tube construction with matte black finish to minimize glare 


Included are a set of Kenton Industries Target Turrets calibrated for this Scope and the  .308 Winchester 168 Grain Boat Tail Hollow Point @ 2700 Feet Per Second. Barrel Length spread is 22"- 26", with 26" being optimum. These turrets make ranging as simple as clicking up 25 yards at a time once 100 yard zero is achieved. The MilDots are round, and their size is .22 mils, U.S. Army Standard.


This scope was used for a one week FBI Sniper Marksmanship Course. It is near mint condition. No box or paperwork. A manual is available online, but only a MilDot User Tutorial is needed to learn the reticle system.


Prefer to sell local so buyer can inspect before purchase.  Thank you for looking!

title: For Sale:  Price Drop Special!!!!   CMMG Piston pistol - SBR build ready!!
postcontent:
600 obo.  Down from $700.  I wanted 600, but somehow started thinking700.  Get in now before it's gone!

I am selling my AR Pistol.  This started out as a CMMG AR, but has morphed into something different over time.  I decided I wanted an SBR, so I was going to use my CMMG lower.  To get away with using it now, I put a pistol buffer tube on it, to make it a "pistol".  Because I have been traveling in and out of the country, I just haven't sat down to do the form, and get lower engraved.  I was going to get my info engraved under the trigger well, almost invisible when filled in black, but still legal.  To finish the SBR portion, you just need to fill out the BATF paperwork, get the receiver engraved, pay the tax, get the stamp, and put a stock on it.  That’s it.

About the weapon.....  CMMG MK-4 lower.  Aero Precision upper.  Daniel Defense 10.3" Government issue 5.56 SBR barrel (1:7 twist).  Magpul handguard with light rail (side mounted for thumb activated light (will include for $75 - INFORCE).  It has a modified stock trigger, still 2 stage, but much better break when it fires.  KNS Anti-rotation pins.  Yankee Hill quick takedown pins.  Rainier Arms AXTS charging handle (I will subtract $50 if you want a stock charging handle).  It has a "knock off" Noveske Flaming Pig flash thingie.  I will also include 2 Magpul parts kits magazines (will not have floor panels).

I had a SIG SB15 Pistol Brace, but a family member visiting decided that he NEEDED it, so he removed it before he left, and stuck a $50 bill on the pistol tube.  He got a good deal.......   Now, since the BATF said that the brace doesn’t change it from a pistol to an SBR, I have seen many, MANY people shooting "pistols" shouldered using the brace.  I would think it would not be comfortable, but functional.

*  I wiped it down with oil before I took the pictures, and I didn’t notice it until I was doing the pictures that not all of the oil was gone.

** For free, I will throw in 2 Magpul floor plates.
